<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Locarno)/394:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-12T17:00:00-05:00">March 12,
                                    1936—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>51. Your March 9, 11 p.m. I have conveyed your message to the President
                            and he asks me to express his appreciation for your suggestion and the
                            spirit in which it is offered and to say that we are following the
                            developments closely and are hopeful that the procedure provided for
                            this situation will obviate any necessity for drastic action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>